{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φῐλοσοφ-ία</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>love of knowledge, pursuit there of, speculation,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.209, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 61a, “Grg.” 484c, +others; ἡ φ. κτῆσις ἐπιστήμης [prev. author] “Euthd.” 288d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; defined as ἄσκησις ἐπιτηδείου τέχνης, Stoic. in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Placita Philosophorum” 1 “Prooem.” 2. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>systematic, methodical treatment</b> of a subject, ἐμπειρίᾳ μέτιθι καὶ φιλοσοφίᾳ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 2.35 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ περὶ τὰς ἔριδας φ. <b>scientific treatment</b> of argumentation, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 10.6 \">Refs</a>]; ἡ περὶ τοὺς λόγους φ. the <b>study</b> of oratory, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 4.10: _plural_, οἱ ἐν ταῖς φ. πολὺν χρόνον διατρίψαντες 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 172c; τέχναι καὶ φ. 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 10.67. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>philosophy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 11.22, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Definitiones” 414b, etc.; ἱστορία φ. ἐστὶν ἐκ παραδειγμάτων 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “Ars Rhetorica” 11.2:— 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator usually prefixes the _Article_, 2.51, 5.84, 7.45 (but compare 2.35 above)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; sometimes also in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus and 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus, as 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 482a, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 993b20, “EN” 1177a25 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], and so later, διὰ τῆς φ. καὶ κενῆς ἀπάτης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Col.2.8 \">NT</a>]; but more frequently without <i>Article</i>, τοῖς ἐν φιλοσοφίᾳ ζῶσιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)